<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,1202,1625]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1454,1480]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[694,834,1454,1481]" name="South Korea" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Byun, B. - K." box="[849,1126,1454,1481]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="75 - 91" refId="ref77325" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Byun, B. - K. (1993) Pamphiliid sawfly genera Neurotoma and Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of Korea. Insecta Koreana, Chuncheon, 10, 75 - 91." type="journal article" year="1993">Shinohara &amp; Byun 1993</bibRefCitation>
) but later found across vast areas of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[348,418,1490,1516]" name="China" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
, where it is more commonly found (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C." box="[819,1080,1490,1516]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="53 - 74" refId="ref79164" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C. (2012) Pamphiliid sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of Mt. Yunshan, Hunan Province, China. Memoirs of the National Museum of Nature and Science, Tokyo, 48, 53 - 74." type="journal article" year="2012">Shinohara &amp; Wei 2012</bibRefCitation>
). It is a member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1334,1436,1491,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wongi">
<emphasis box="[1334,1436,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">O. wongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of the 
<taxonomicName box="[329,432,1527,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wongi">
<emphasis box="[329,432,1527,1553]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">O. wongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName box="[626,781,1526,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteicornis">
<emphasis box="[626,781,1526,1553]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">O. luteicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1132,1526,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wongi">
<emphasis box="[921,1132,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Onycholyda wongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex is represented by seven species (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kiyoshi, T. &amp; Wei, M. - C. &amp; Kameda, Y." box="[318,577,1562,1588]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="75 - 81" refId="ref78172" refString="Shinohara, A., Kiyoshi, T., Wei, M. - C. &amp; Kameda, Y. (2018 c) Identification of larvae and recognition of new synonymy for two Chinese Onycholyda sawflies (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Pamphiliidae) based on molecular data. Species Diversity, 23, 75 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 23.75" type="journal article" year="2018">
Shinohara 
<emphasis box="[441,498,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
2018c
</bibRefCitation>
), all confined to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[871,941,1562,1588]" name="China" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
, except for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Byun" authorityYear="1993" box="[1073,1215,1562,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odaesana">
<emphasis box="[1073,1215,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">O. odaesana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Byun" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odaesana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Onycholyda odaesana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1890" box="[335,483,1598,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pamphiliidae</taxonomicName>
known so far to occur both in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[930,997,1598,1624]" name="China" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1123,1599,1625]" name="South Korea" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
